President Obama has honored 102 mathematics and science teachers with the Presidential Award for Excellence in Mathematics and Science Teaching. The winners, who teach K-12, were selected by a panel of scientists, mathematicians, and educators. Each winner will receive a $10,000 award from the National Science Foundation and will be invited to a ceremony in Washington, DC. President Obama emphasized the importance of excellent math and science teachers in inspiring students to pursue STEM fields. He has set a goal to prepare 100,000 science and math teachers over the next decade and has proposed launching a STEM Master Teacher Corps. Nominations for the 2014 Presidential Award for Excellence in Mathematics and Science Teaching are open until April 1, 2014.